.TH PUNK_OS 1 "2024" "Punk_OS 1.0" "Punk_OS Manual"
.SH NAME
punk_os \- Ubuntu development environment setup and reference system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B setup.sh
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.br
.B check-installed.sh
[\fIoutput-file\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Punk_OS
is a comprehensive development environment setup script for Ubuntu and Ubuntu-based distributions (including Pop!_OS, Linux Mint, Elementary OS, and others). It transforms a fresh installation into a fully-equipped development machine with programming languages, IDEs, CLI tools, and productivity applications.

The system includes two main components:
.TP
.B setup.sh
Interactive installer that sets up your development environment
.TP
.B check-installed.sh
Generates a reference manual of installed software

.SH OPTIONS
.SS setup.sh options:
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Run in non-interactive mode. Automatically accepts all installation prompts.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information and exit.

.SS check-installed.sh options:
.TP
.I output-file
Optional filename for the generated reference manual (default: INSTALLED.md)

