.RE

.SH POST-INSTALLATION

After running setup.sh, you should:

.IP 1. 3
\fBLog out and back in\fR (or reboot) for all changes to take effect
.IP 2. 3
Configure GNOME Extensions using GNOME Tweaks
.IP 3. 3
Set up your terminal (Alacritty config at ~/.config/alacritty/alacritty.yml)
.IP 4. 3
Configure your dotfiles repository if you have one

.SH TROUBLESHOOTING

.SS Docker Permission Denied
Log out and back in for group changes to take effect, or run:
.PP
.nf
.RS
newgrp docker
.RE
.fi

.SS Command Not Found
Source your shell configuration or open a new terminal:
.PP
.nf
.RS
source ~/.bashrc
.RE
.fi

.SS nvm Command Not Found
Restart your terminal or run:
.PP
.nf
.RS
source ~/.bashrc
.RE
.fi

.SS Script Fails Midway
The script uses 'set -e' to exit on errors. If it fails:
.IP 1. 3
Check the error message
.IP 2. 3
Fix the issue (often network-related)
.IP 3. 3
Re-run the script - it will skip already installed items

